4. Comparisons & Analysis

Iteration & layer weight: Higher iterations and stronger weights → more intense hallucinations; reducing them preserves original image.

Layer selection: Early layers produce texture-like patterns; later layers introduce structured, object-like features.

Octaves & octave scale: More octaves and higher scale → exaggerated effects; fewer octaves preserve color and shape.

Jitter: Reducing jitter stabilizes hallucinations and prevents artifacts.

TV loss: Ensures smooth patterns, reducing high-frequency noise.

The progression from Version 1 → Version 4 shows how tuning parameters can control hallucination intensity and preserve the original image, providing hands-on insight into Deep Dream mechanics.



| Version | Iterations | LR    | Octaves | Octave Scale | Layers & Weights                                                          | Jitter | Observations                                                                                                    |
| ------- | ---------- | ----- | ------- | ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1       | 50         | 0.01  | 5       | 1.4          | {'inception4a': 1.0}                                                      | 32     | Strong hallucinations, hypnotic circles, eyes, original image almost invisible                                  |
| 2       | 25         | 0.01  | 3       | 1.2          | {'inception4a': 0.5}                                                      | 32     | Original shapes visible, patterns & eyes still present, hypnotic circles reduced                                |
| 3       | 30         | 0.008 | 3       | 1.2          | {'inception4a':0.3,'inception4e':0.7}                                     | 16     | Original shapes visible, hallucinated eyes less frequent, triangular patterns appear, better overall balance    |
| 4       | 20         | 0.008 | 3       | 1.0          | {'inception3a':0.1,'inception4a':0.2,'inception4d':0.3,'inception4e':0.4} | 16     | Original image mostly preserved, hallucinations subtle, eyes, triangles, soft RGB colors, slow fluctuating loss |




5. Conclusion

Deep Dream can transform images from subtle texture enhancement to surreal, highly hallucinatory visuals.

Parameter tuning allows control over pattern intensity, original image preservation, and visual style.

Combining layers at different depths creates more visually appealing and structured hallucinations.

Final version demonstrates a subtle enhancement, preserving original image colors while adding artistic patterns.

This lab provides practical experience with pretrained CNNs, feature visualization, and neural network interpretability.
